1
00:00:04,900 --> 00:00:09,889
We know Gurudev’s being 
super affectionate, and it’s true.

2
00:00:09,889 --> 00:00:15,597
He’s love and affectionate personified,
really, truly, to the extreme.

3
00:00:15,597 --> 00:00:18,357
[Extreme Tolerance]

4
00:00:18,357 --> 00:00:23,382
And how he backs his devotees.
He goes through hell with them.

5
00:00:23,382 --> 00:00:25,779
And all these things.

6
00:00:26,129 --> 00:00:30,019
And being with people like myself
that’s a likelihood.

7
00:00:30,019 --> 00:00:34,660
It’s not just like 
a saying of flattery.

8
00:00:34,660 --> 00:00:37,430
But anyway, 
when he was younger …

9
00:00:37,448 --> 00:00:42,148
Guru Mahārāj  
could be super affectionate

10
00:00:42,148 --> 00:00:46,894
and loving, and it’s really true;
totally charming and all that,

11
00:00:46,894 --> 00:00:50,629
but He’s also very …
he could be very severe.

12
00:00:50,629 --> 00:00:53,119
That was his word 
about himself.
 

13
00:00:53,129 --> 00:00:55,339
Because when they said 
sometime like,

14
00:00:55,339 --> 00:00:59,004
“He made some comments
about this or that.”

15
00:00:59,004 --> 00:01:04,934
He once said,
“I’m a man, who if I was in Vaikuṇṭha,

16
00:01:04,934 --> 00:01:09,373
I would be a troublemaker.
I would cause dissension.”

17
00:01:09,373 --> 00:01:12,712
And like, if he was in Vaikuṇṭha,
people were going like …

18
00:01:12,712 --> 00:01:15,796
he’s saying something higher
than we were actually …

19
00:01:15,796 --> 00:01:20,571
Like, that would be trouble.
He said, again he said us about himself.

20
00:01:20,571 --> 00:01:23,172
Another time something came up,
and we were trying,

21
00:01:23,172 --> 00:01:24,620
‘Oh, no Mahārāj , 
you are this …’

22
00:01:24,620 --> 00:01:30,260
And he goes, ‘No, I’m 
a severe commentator.’” That he said.

23
00:01:30,260 --> 00:01:32,488
Once some people 
came to him and said,
 

24
00:01:32,488 --> 00:01:34,288
what they’re trying
to find something to go,

25
00:01:34,288 --> 00:01:37,878
“There’s some letter
at the Alabahat Gaudia Math,

26
00:01:37,878 --> 00:01:41,376
it says you’re a troublemaker, 
you did …”

27
00:01:41,376 --> 00:01:44,841
And Guru Mahārāj  
is like leaning on the wall,

28
00:01:44,841 --> 00:01:47,274
and these persons 
giving this report,
 

29
00:01:47,274 --> 00:01:52,698
“There’s a letter somewhere, that says—
troublemaker and cause dissension.”

30
00:01:52,698 --> 00:01:55,441
Guru Mahārāj , when it finally was clear,
what’s being said.

31
00:01:55,441 --> 00:02:00,409
He went, “I accept the challenge.”
[Laughing]
 

32
00:02:00,409 --> 00:02:04,359
He said, “Yes, whenever things 
are not up to mark,

33
00:02:04,359 --> 00:02:10,913
I say so, and boldly I say so.
Therefore I’m alone. ”

34
00:02:13,743 --> 00:02:16,476
And we were going like, “But we’re happy 
to be with you Mahārāj .”

35
00:02:16,476 --> 00:02:20,886
[Laughing]

36
00:02:21,937 --> 00:02:27,371
So, but also he could be severe.
Gurudev, one of the reasons
 

37
00:02:27,371 --> 00:02:30,001
Gurudev was so tolerant 
with everyone,
 

38
00:02:30,001 --> 00:02:33,001
it’s only one reason, 
there are many.

39
00:02:33,001 --> 00:02:35,960
But he said, 
and he meant this,

40
00:02:35,960 --> 00:02:39,280
not as a statement 
of humility, but like …

41
00:02:39,280 --> 00:02:43,004
He said, “Guru Mahārāj  
was so tolerant with me,

42
00:02:43,004 --> 00:02:47,404
how can I turn around and
not be tolerant with you and others.”

43
00:02:47,417 --> 00:02:49,872
That was a very beautiful
way of thinking.

44
00:02:49,872 --> 00:02:52,406
He’s saying, “I know how much …”
And he’s saying that.

45
00:02:52,406 --> 00:02:56,375
I mean you can adjust it
in anyway you want

46
00:02:56,375 --> 00:03:02,975
according to your conception.
But he did say this.

47
00:03:02,975 --> 00:03:08,002
So, that’s way to say, “Guru Mahārāj ’s 
just unlimited tolerant and affectionate.

48
00:03:08,002 --> 00:03:13,441
So I have to, I feel I should do that
with all of you and others, and like that.”

